 					http://www.history.com/news/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/offering-chapel.jpg
                    
					An offering chapel built during the Middle Kingdom period was one of many structures that Egyptians from all levels of society built along a processional route at Abydos. It was likely devoted to the god of the underworld and afterlife, Osiris. (Credit: Mary-Ann Pouls Wegner)
