					Animal Mummy Repository
                    
 					http://www.history.com/news/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/mummy-repository.jpg
                    
					A large structure probably once served as a temple and was later used as a repository for animal mummies. Its mud bricks still bear traces of plaster and whitewash. (Credit: Mary-Ann Pouls Wegner)
